   <title>Day 1: The Icy Threshold</title>
   <link href="https://riddleverse.franciscogc.com/stories/christmas2024/act1/day-1-the-icy-threshold/"/>
   <updated>2023-12-01T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
   <id>https://riddleverse.franciscogc.com/stories/christmas2024/act1/the-icy-threshold</id>
   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The riddle etched into the gates reads:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;I am not alive, but I grow; I don’t have lungs, but I need air; I don’t have a mouth, but I can drown. What am I?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;details&gt;
 &lt;summary&gt;Hint 1&lt;/summary&gt;
 &quot;I thrive on fuel but vanish in water.&quot;
&lt;/details&gt;

&lt;details&gt;
 &lt;summary&gt;Hint 2&lt;/summary&gt;
 &quot;I&apos;m used to warm homes and light the way in darkness.&quot;
&lt;/details&gt;
</content>
